track.name: It's Nobody's Fault But Mine
comments: such emotion from that huge voice

Agrees with Oppressotron: "One part gospel, one part proto-rock, this song is transcendent. Yep, we’re all familiar with the Zeppelin version but you get the real essence and emotion from Blind Willie’s track that is missing from the cover. It’s just such good slide action!!!! "
I love Zeppelin's version but I love this one even more. It sounds much more authentic. So much raw emotion.
language will never do Blind Willie Johnson justice.

Yes, this fantastic yet Grossly undervalued street preacher died of penumonia after his house burned down, was refused treatment by the white doctors in town and laid down upon the sopping wet bed that was left from the fire hoses. That's the real blues.
I had no idea that Led Zep's was a cover
he was killed by weather, so they say.
